## Filtering

### Basic Filtering

```typescript
const csv = `name,age,salary,department
Alice,28,60000,Engineering
Bob,35,75000,Sales
Charlie,24,55000,Engineering
Diana,42,95000,Sales
Eve,31,70000,Engineering`;

const result = parseCSV(csv);

// Filter by age
const over30 = result.filter(row => row.age > 30);
console.log(`People over 30: ${over30.count()}`);

// Filter by department
const engineers = result.filter(row => row.department === 'Engineering');
console.log(`Engineers: ${engineers.count()}`);

// Filter by salary
const highEarners = result.filter(row => row.salary > 70000);
console.log(`Earning over $70k: ${highEarners.count()}`);
```

### Chained Filtering

```typescript
// Find senior engineers with high salary
const seniorHighEarning = result
  .filter(row => row.department === 'Engineering')
  .filter(row => row.age > 30)
  .filter(row => row.salary > 70000);

console.log(seniorHighEarning.rows);
```

### Complex Predicates

```typescript
// Filter with multiple conditions
const filtered = result.filter(row => 
  (row.department === 'Engineering' || row.department === 'Sales') &&
  row.salary >= 60000 &&
  row.age >= 25
);

console.log(`${filtered.count()} employees match criteria`);
```

### Filter Using Index

```typescript
// Get every other row
